%T A116134 3829098407015032018435618903285,1017438814759112270449904796121753809
%N A116134 Numbers k such that k concatenated with k-3 gives the product of two numbers which differ by 1.
%C A116134 If k-3 has d digits, the concatenation is k//k-3 = 10^d*k+k-3 = m*(m+1), therefore k//k-5 = 10^d*k+k-5 = (m-1)*(m+2), so there is a large overlap (or equality) with A116122, and k//k-9 = 10^d*k+k-9 = (m-2)*(m+3), so there is a large overlap (or equality) with A116097. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
%e A116134 92185//92182 = 96013 * 96014, where // denotes concatenation.
%Y A116134 Cf. A116097, A116120, A115431, A116141, A116265.
%K A116134 nonn,base,more
%O A116134 1,1
